BULLET::::- "&lt;a href="http%3A//www.reuters.com/newsArticle.jhtml%3FstoryID%3D7784062"&gt;BBC Self-Governance Scrapped in Government Proposal&lt;/a&gt;" — &lt;i&gt;&lt;span class="interwiki-link-foreign"&gt;&lt;a href="w%3AReuters"&gt;Reuters&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/i&gt;, March 2, 2005
BULLET::::- Tara Conlan. "&lt;a href="http%3A//media.guardian.co.uk/site/story/0%2C14173%2C1428548%2C00.html%3Fgusrc%3Drss"&gt;BBC governors axed, licence fee to stay&lt;/a&gt;" — &lt;i&gt;&lt;span class="interwiki-link-foreign"&gt;&lt;a href="w%3AThe%20Guardian"&gt;The Guardian&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/i&gt;, March 2, 2005
BULLET::::- Andrew Woodcock and Anita Singh. "&lt;a href="http%3A//news.independent.co.uk/media/story.jsp%3Fstory%3D616137"&gt;Government plans to abolish BBC governors, but licence given 10-year extension&lt;/a&gt;" — &lt;i&gt;&lt;span class="interwiki-link-foreign"&gt;&lt;a href="w%3AThe%20Independent"&gt;The Independent&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/i&gt;, March 2, 2005

