<doc id="5342" url="https://en.wikinews.org/wiki?curid=5342" title="Take-Two Interactive profits surge 74%">
<h1>Take-Two Interactive profits surge 74%</h1>
&lt;strong class="published"&gt;&lt;span id="publishDate" class="value-title" title=""&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class="Z3988" style="display:none" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rfr_id=rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:User%3ADendodge&amp;rft_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:&amp;rft.atitle=Take-Two%20Interactive%20profits%20surge%2074%25&amp;rft.jtitle=Wikinews&amp;rft.date=&amp;rft.aucorp=Wikinews+contributors&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.rights=CC-BY+2.5&amp;rft.identifier=&amp;rft.artnum="&gt; &lt;/span&gt; 
&lt;a href="w%3ATake%20Two%20Interactive"&gt;Take-Two&lt;/a&gt;, the company behind the &lt;a href="w%3AGrand%20Theft%20Auto%20%28series%29"&gt;Grand Theft Auto video game franchise&lt;/a&gt;, has reported a 74% rise in quarterly profits. The company also revealed that sales of its bestselling product; ♡❤&lt;a href="w%3AGrand%20Theft%20Auto%3A%20San%20Andreas"&gt;Grand Theft Auto: San Andreas&lt;/a&gt;♡❤ had surpassed 12 million copies.

The company stated that profits were $55.2m up from $31.8m in the same quarter last year. Per share earnings were $1.19, comfortably ahead of analyst expectations of $1.09 a share. Sales also rose substantially, from $375.5m to $502.5m. 

Despite the news shares in Take-Two drifted $0.45 lower to $37.42 due to the company forecasting a loss of 20 cents a share for the coming quarter.

