BULLET::::- "&lt;a href="http%3A//news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/programmes/question_time/4335687.stm"&gt;Chinese audience joins TV debate&lt;/a&gt;" — &lt;i&gt;&lt;span class="interwiki-link-foreign"&gt;&lt;a href="w%3ABBC%20News"&gt;BBC News&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/i&gt;, March 11, 2005
BULLET::::- "&lt;a href="http%3A//news.xinhuanet.com/english/2005-03/11/content_2683443.htm"&gt;BBC political debate aired from Shanghai&lt;/a&gt;" — &lt;i&gt;&lt;span class="interwiki-link-foreign"&gt;&lt;a href="w%3AXinhua"&gt;Xinhua&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/i&gt;, March 11, 2005
BULLET::::- Richard Spencer. "&lt;a href="http%3A//www.telegraph.co.uk/news/main.jhtml%3Fxml%3D/news/2005/03/11/wchin11.xml%26amp%3BsSheet%3D/news/2005/03/11/ixnewstop.html"&gt;China joins the BBC for a Question Time from Shanghai&lt;/a&gt;" — &lt;i&gt;&lt;span class="interwiki-link-foreign"&gt;&lt;a href="w%3AThe%20Daily%20Telegraph%20%28UK%29"&gt;The Daily Telegraph (UK)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/i&gt;, March 11, 2005

</ul>


