<doc id="5794" url="https://en.wikinews.org/wiki?curid=5794" title="Cookbook is free reference work community's most active project">
<h1>Cookbook is free reference work community's most active project</h1>
&lt;strong class="published"&gt;&lt;span id="publishDate" class="value-title" title=""&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class="Z3988" style="display:none" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rfr_id=rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:User%3ADendodge&amp;rft_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:&amp;rft.atitle=Cookbook%20is%20free%20reference%20work%20community%27s%20most%20active%20project&amp;rft.jtitle=Wikinews&amp;rft.date=&amp;rft.aucorp=Wikinews+contributors&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.rights=CC-BY+2.5&amp;rft.identifier=&amp;rft.artnum="&gt; &lt;/span&gt; 
, an Internet project which seeks to create &lt;a href="w%3Afree%20content"&gt;free content&lt;/a&gt; textbooks using &lt;a href="w%3Awiki"&gt;wiki technology&lt;/a&gt;, has published its February 2005 statistics. The project leads the statistics, both by number of contributors (94) and by total edits (668). Newcomer of the month is "", with 337 edits by mainly one user, followed by "" (320 edits). Seventy contributors edited on "", followed by sixty-eight users on the "". Wikiversity is a project of its own which aims to build a collaborative learning environment online. 

Wikibooks was originally meant as a place for textbooks and manuals but has increasingly become a community creating books on all kinds of subjects, with the cookbook being the most prominent example. Intended as a ♡❤collection of recipes from around the world♡❤, it hosts recipes from to , ethnic cuisines from the to the , and gives background information on ingredients, nutrition, and many cooking techniques.

Wikis are openly editable websites that are often used to create knowledge bases. Wikibooks is a project operated by the &lt;a href="w%3AWikimedia"&gt;Wikimedia Foundation&lt;/a&gt;, a non-profit organization based in the &lt;a href="w%3AUnited%20States"&gt;United States&lt;/a&gt; which runs several free content wikis, including &lt;a href="w%3AWikipedia"&gt;Wikipedia&lt;/a&gt;, a free encyclopedia, and &lt;a href="w%3AWikinews"&gt;Wikinews&lt;/a&gt;, a free news source. The statistics for Wikibooks are extracted using an &lt;a href="w%3ASQL"&gt;SQL&lt;/a&gt; query on the latest Wikibooks &lt;a href="w%3Adatabase"&gt;database&lt;/a&gt; dump. 

<h2>Source</h2>

&lt;a href="http%3A//en.wikibooks.org/wiki/Wikibooks%3ATop_active"&gt;Top active statistics on Wikibooks&lt;/a&gt;

♡❤Originally based on an anonymous .♡❤


