<doc id="5939" url="https://en.wikinews.org/wiki?curid=5939" title="Irish mobile penetration rate hits 94%">
<h1>Irish mobile penetration rate hits 94%</h1>
&lt;strong class="published"&gt;&lt;span id="publishDate" class="value-title" title=""&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class="Z3988" style="display:none" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rfr_id=rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:User%3ADendodge&amp;rft_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:&amp;rft.atitle=Irish%20mobile%20penetration%20rate%20hits%2094%25&amp;rft.jtitle=Wikinews&amp;rft.date=&amp;rft.aucorp=Wikinews+contributors&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.rights=CC-BY+2.5&amp;rft.identifier=&amp;rft.artnum="&gt; &lt;/span&gt; 

According to a quarterly report by &lt;a href="w%3AComReg"&gt;ComReg&lt;/a&gt; (Commission for Communications Regulation) on the &lt;a href="w%3ARepublic%20of%20Ireland"&gt;Irish&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="w%3Atelecommunications"&gt;telecommunications&lt;/a&gt; market released today, Irish &lt;a href="w%3Amobile%20phone"&gt;mobile phone&lt;/a&gt; penetration has hit a new record of 94%. This is an increase of 6% from the same time last year, when penetration rates stood at 88%. The statistic means that there are now 3.78 million mobile phone subscribers in Ireland. The document also indicated that the number of &lt;a href="w%3ABroadband%20Internet%20access"&gt;broadband&lt;/a&gt; customers in Ireland now stands at 131,550.

Among other things the statistics revealed that:
<ul>
BULLET::::- ♡❤♡94%♡❤♡ of Irish people own a mobile phone - up from 88% last year,
BULLET::::- There are now ♡❤♡131,550♡❤♡ broadband connections, an increase of 37% in the last quarter,
BULLET::::- The Irish fixed, mobile and broadcasting market is now worth ♡❤♡€4bn per annum♡❤♡,
BULLET::::- Over ♡❤♡1bn♡❤♡ &lt;a href="w%3Atext%20messages"&gt;text messages&lt;/a&gt; are now sent every quarter.

</ul>
Earlier this week &lt;a href="w%3AEircom"&gt;Eircom&lt;/a&gt;, the largest broadband provider in the country announced that it intends to double its standard packages speed from 512kps to 1Mbps. Also Meteor has announced that it would consider allowing a &lt;a href="w%3AMobile%20Virtual%20Network%20Operator"&gt;Mobile Virtual Network Operator&lt;/a&gt; (MVNO) to piggyback on its network.

